Based on Warren's deeply introspective and previously unexplored diaries, Angel on a Freight Train traces his youthful freedom and sensuality, his attempt to join with younger men in a spirit of loving mentorship, and, finally, the tortured introspection of a man whose age seemed to shut him out from an idyllic lost world. In the end, Warren came to believe rather sorrowfully in a radical division between his angelic, ideal self and what he called "the freight train of animal life below."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChristian gay menvBiography. 0aGay college teachersvBiography. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aHistory : History. 4aLiterature : Nineteenth-Century Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847996540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438479965423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438479965/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles